** Emacs

You can use <b><i>`M-x check-parens'</i></b> to find any unbalanced parentheses and unbalanced string quotes in the buffer.

 - `C-M-f' Move forward over a balanced expression (`forward-sexp').

 - `C-M-b' Move backward over a balanced expression(`backward-sexp').

 - `C-M-k' Kill balanced expression forward (`kill-sexp').

 - `C-M-DEL' Kill balanced expression backward (`backward-kill-sexp').

 - `C-M-t' Transpose expressions (`transpose-sexps').

 - `C-M-@' Put mark after following expression (`mark-sexp').

