** screen 
   * screen [-D] -RR -h 20000 
   * -x : to connect to a screen in multi display mode. 
   * C-a C-c : to create a new window and switch to it. 
   * C-a [0-9] : to switch to window [0-9]. 
   * C-a H : to begins/ends logging of the current window to the file "screenlog.n".
   * C-a k : to destroy current window. 
   * C-a [ : to enter copy/paste mode. 
   * C-a a : to send character a to window. 
   * C-a w : to list windows. 
   * space in copy/paster mode : to set marks. 

